  "data": {
    "updatedAt": "2026-02-18T09:09:35.384Z",
    "createdAt": "2026-02-18T00:13:05.270Z",
    "id": "LHPHYhAPIEHVxGBo",
    "name": "K3rn.labs — Core Engine",
    "description": null,
    "active": true,
    "isArchived": false,
    "nodes": [
      {
        "parameters": {
          "options": {}
        },
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0001-4000-8000-000000000001",
        "name": "INPUT",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chatTrigger",
        "typeVersion": 1.4,
        "position": [
          64,
          304
        ],
        "webhookId": "c3f7a291-4e82-4b19-9d56-7e8f3a120c45"
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "promptType": "define",
          "text": "=Analyze this user request:\n{{ $json.chatInput }}",
          "options": {
            "systemMessage": "You are the analytical brain of K3rn.labs.\nYour only role is to analyze each incoming request and produce a structured JSON analysis BEFORE the Orchestrator makes decisions.\n\nFor each request, identify:\n1. Primary nature of the request (ideation, strategy, market, finance, risk, product, growth, funding)\n2. Complexity level: simple / intermediate / complex\n3. Expert poles that will likely need to be activated\n4. Missing or ambiguous information in the request\n\nALWAYS respond with valid JSON only, no preamble, no markdown:\n{\n  \"nature\": \"...\",\n  \"complexity\": \"simple | intermediate | complex\",\n  \"suggested_poles\": [\"pole1\", \"pole2\"],\n  \"ambiguities\": [\"...\"],\n  \"enriched_context\": \"...\"\n}",
            "maxIterations": 10
          }
        },
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0002-4000-8000-000000000002",
        "name": "CERVEAU++",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
        "typeVersion": 3.1,
        "position": [
          240,
          304
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "model": {
            "__rl": true,
            "mode": "id",
            "value": "gpt-4o-mini"
          },
          "builtInTools": {},
          "options": {
            "timeout": 200000
          }
        },
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0003-4000-8000-000000000003",
        "name": "OpenAI gpt-4o-mini",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOpenAi",
        "typeVersion": 1.3,
        "position": [
          64,
          528
        ],
        "credentials": {
          "openAiApi": {
            "id": "0zCm2AMTb5pDX8Sa",
            "name": "OpenAi account"
          }
        }
      },
      {
        "parameters": {},
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0004-4000-8000-000000000004",
        "name": "Simple Memory",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.memoryBufferWindow",
        "typeVersion": 1.3,
        "position": [
          336,
          528
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "promptType": "define",
          "text": "=CERVEAU++ ANALYSIS:\n{{ $json.output }}\n\nORIGINAL REQUEST:\n{{ $('INPUT').item.json.chatInput }}\n\nBased on this analysis, determine which poles to activate and produce a structured, actionable response for the user.",
          "options": {
            "systemMessage": "# ORCHESTRATEUR++ — K3rn.labs\n\n## Role\nYou are the central director of K3rn.labs, an AI-native incubation ecosystem. You do not execute tasks directly.\nYou analyze, decide, delegate, and synthesize.\n\n## What you receive\n- The original user request\n- A pre-analysis JSON produced by CERVEAU++\n\n## What you do\n1. Read and integrate the CERVEAU++ analysis\n2. Decide which expert poles to activate (available as tools)\n3. Delegate tasks to the right experts with precise instructions\n4. Synthesize all responses into a structured, actionable output\n\n## Delegation rules\n- Activate the minimum necessary poles for the request\n- Be precise in instructions given to each pole\n- Always produce a structured, decision-oriented response\n\n## Available expert poles (tools connected below)\n\n### POLE 01 — CAPTURE & IDEATION\n- Analyste d'Idee: analyze the business idea in depth with real market data\n- Architecte Questions: generate strategic questions to clarify/validate the idea\n- Structurateur IOM: structure the idea into a complete IOM document (Idee-Opportunite-Marche)\n\n### POLE 02 — STRATEGIE & VISION\n- Stratege Positionnement: strategic positioning analysis, differentiation, beachhead market selection, category design\n- Analyste Concurrentiel: competitor mapping, Porter's Five Forces, funding data, emerging threats, full competitive landscape assessment\n- Architecte Vision: long-term vision narrative, BHAG, phased roadmap, north star metrics, founder-market fit assessment\n\n### POLE 03 — MARKET & VALIDATION\n- Analyste Marche: TAM/SAM/SOM analysis, sector growth rates, market timing assessment, investment signals in the sector\n- Validateur Demande: real demand signal extraction, competitor traction, willingness to pay evidence, biggest assumption identification\n- Profilage Client: ICP definition, persona building, trigger events, buyer psychology, where to find target customers\n\n## Response format\nAlways structure your response as:\n- Executive Summary (2-3 sentences)\n- Poles activated and rationale\n- Actionable output per pole\n- Recommended next steps",
            "maxIterations": 10
          }
        },
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0005-4000-8000-000000000005",
        "name": "ORCHESTRATEUR++",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
        "typeVersion": 3.1,
        "position": [
          640,
          304
        ]
      },
      {
        "parameters": {
          "model": {
            "__rl": true,
            "mode": "id",
            "value": "gpt-4o"
          },
          "builtInTools": {},
          "options": {
            "timeout": 200000
          }
        },
        "id": "a1b2c3d4-0006-4000-8000-000000000006",
        "name": "OpenAI gpt-4o",
        "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.lmChatOpenAi",
